tags: don't read this if you haven't watched endgame!
but she made her choices and we have to respect that
she hoped the red of her blood would wipe out the red in her ledger
body:
SPOILERS FOR AVENGERS ENDGAME

I told myself I wouldn’t post spoilers for Endgame until at least two weeks afterwards but I just had to get this out.

You know how in Endgame, when Natasha sacrifices herself for the Soul Stone, we don’t really see her falling, unlike Gamora? We just see her body at the bottom of the cliff

I’m willing to bet money that Natasha was doing everything in her power to not use her training, both her Red Room and Avenger training, to stop herself from twisting and rolling to avoid fractures and broken bones, just the way she’d twist and turn in the Avengers compound when she trained with Clint and Steve.

I’m willing to bet that she was flinching, twitching, her body convulsing automatically, her legs curling up on muscle memory for half a second before she got her control and told herself that she was doing this for Clint, for his family, for her family, even though she’d never see them again.

I’m willing to bet that as Natasha was falling, her body was screaming at her to tuck and roll to ensure minimum damage, but her mind was telling her to let herself freefall and look up to see Clint’s face one last time before her blood joined the other stains at the bottom of the cliff.

I’m willing to bet that there was a part of Natasha that allowed her to deliver a soft smile and finally hope that her sacrifice would be enough to wipe out the red in her ledger.
